It’s finally here! 🎉 “The Dominican Kitchen” cookbook is now available on pre-sale. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This book is a collection of more than 80 authentic, traditional recipes inspired by my heritage and upbringing in the Dominican Republic. Created with easy-to-find ingredients and featuring comforting traditional flavors, my recipes are designed for modern families who don’t have tons of time to spend perfecting a classic recipe but who want to feed their families well every day.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m ecstatic and so proud of the work that went into creating this project. This cookbook is a labor of love ❤️ for my culture and my community because our stories and recipes deserve space on bookshelves all over the world. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“The Dominican Kitchen” will be published on May 2, 2023, and it’s now available for preorder!

This delicious frozen mango margarita is so easy to make with just a handful of ingredients. Made super smooth in my new @Vitamix blender, this refreshing cocktail is ready in about 5 minutes!

Vitamix blenders last 10x longer than the average blender, and they’re built to handle the toughest ingredients, blend after blend. I’m in love with this blender! 

Check the link in bio to get yours and make this cocktail!

Ingredients: 
4 cups frozen mango
6 oz. tequila
2 oz. orange liquor
2 oz. agave syrup
2 tablespoons fresh lime juice
1-2 tablespoons Tajín

Instructions:
Rub a lime wedge around the edge of your glasses, then dip the rim in the Tajín and twist to coat.
Blend the mango, tequila, orange liquor, agave, and lime juice for about 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until smooth. 

Enjoy!

I’M BACK!!! … Life update 👇🏽
It’s been a while since I showed up here, but let me tell you in 2023 life was lifing for real! Specially the last 2 months of the year when I was on vacation in my beautiful island and ended up getting surgery there. And no, I didn’t get a tummy tuck or a BBL 🙄

The universe literally forced me to slow down. No, actually, it forced me to do a complete stop ✋🏼, laid me on my back (literally) for over a month and I couldn’t do anything about it but be patient and GRATEFUL. 

I’m still recovering but already starting to feel much more like myself. Looking forward to what 2024 has in store for me as I plan for a life with ease. 

EASE is my word for the year, y’all. 🙌🏽

I’m going to be showing up here more just please be patient with me as I recover and work my way through the ropes again. 

In the meantime, I leave you with these photos I took from the only time I was able to visit the beach (my favorite place) while in DR, four weeks after my surgery. It was the first time I left the house after getting surgery and chose to go there because I just needed to smell the sea 🌊 

Anyways, I missed y’all!!
